The Nigerian fin-tech space has generated a lot of attention in the past few years with new entrants vying strongly for the consumer’s interest with exciting features. One of such new entrants is Octa. Octa is an online saving and investment platform that allows users to save towards their dreams. Users enjoy a higher interest rate while the lacuna of a poor savings culture in the country is being filled. The post Octa App set to become the preferred online savings platform in Nigeria appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News – Nigeria and World News. Source: Guardian